parameters.name: SPACECRAFT CLOCK
parameters.description:
Spacecraft clock value of the sample time in the form:                  
      partition/rim:mod91:mod10:mod8 where partition is the number of times   
      the clock modulo counters have rolled over plus one, rim is the major   
      frame counter (~60 2/3 sec), mod91 is the minor frame counter           
      (~2/3 sec, valid = 0-90), mod10 is the real-time interupt (RTI) counter 
      (valid = 0-9), and mod8 is the sub-interupt counter (valid = 0-7).      
      SCLK strings can be converted to UTC by using the SPICE spacecraft      
      clock and leapseconds kernels.
